  "prompt": "Why is Franz Ferdinand famous?",
  "response": "Franz Ferdinand is most famously known as the Archduke of Austria-Este, whose assassination in 1914 is often cited as a major catalyst for the outbreak of World War I. He was the heir presumptive to the Austro-Hungarian throne. His assassination, along with his wife Sophie, Duchess of Hohenberg, on June 28, 1914, in Sarajevo by Gavrilo Princip, a Bosnian Serb nationalist, set off a chain of events that led to the mobilization of European powers and the start of the war. This pivotal moment had profound consequences for global history, marking the beginning of widespread conflict in the 20th century.",
